article.description: Brittany Rayburn scored 22 points and Lindsay Wisdom-Hylton added 20 as Purdue (No. 23 ESPN/USA Today, No. 19 AP) rolled over Hawaii 90-74 at the Waikiki Beach Marriot Classic on Saturday.
article.headline: Purdue rebounds from loss by rolling past Hawaii
article.linkText: Rayburn, Wisdom-Hylton help No. 23 Purdue roll
article.story:
HONOLULU -- Brittany Rayburn scored 22 points and Lindsay Wisdom-Hylton added 20 as Purdue (No. 23 ESPN/USA Today, No. 19 AP) rolled over Hawaii 90-74 at the Waikiki Beach Marriot Classic on Saturday.

Jodi Howell scored 19 for the Boilermakers.

Purdue (4-1) quickly opened an 11-2 lead in the first three minutes. Hawaii got within four, but was never able to take the lead.

Keisha Kanekoa led Hawaii with 21 points, followed by Megan Tinnin with 19. Dita Liepkalne had 12 rebounds for the Rainbow Wahine.

Purdue was coming off a 78-70 overtime loss to No. 5 Stanford on Friday.
